{"name":"Lightning Attack","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s speed with weapons is unmatched, allowing him to launch flurries of attacks in melee. He can make the Lightning Attack action (see page 222).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Swift Attack","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Character may make many melee attacks with single roll.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1uFXOkKxjWE0CpmT"}
{"name":"Hull Down","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte remains aware of his foes at all times in combat, carefully angling his vehicle or steed at each moment to present a narrower silhouette to all attackers, as well as taking the best advantage of any intervening terrain to gain cover. When the character takes a vehicle combat action with the Movement subtype, his vehicle or steed counts the value of its Size trait as being one lower for purposes of attack modifiers and the benefits of cover until the start of his next turn.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill","aptitudes":"Agility, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Reduce size of vehicle while doing combat movement","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4gNuRI8F28M9513O"}
{"name":"Adamantium Faith","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has become inured to horrors that would cripple lesser men. This might come from years of facing incoming fire, staring down the terrors of the Warp, or simply his absolute faith in the Emperor. He can subtract his Willpower bonus from his degrees of failure on a failed Fear or Pinning test. If this reduces the result to zero or less, he counts as having passed the Fear test with 1 degree of success.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Jaded, Resistance (Fear), Willpower 45","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"Reduces DoF from failed Pinning and Fear tests.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"50VTH4SuaHPE4oWB"}
{"name":"Aegis of Contempt","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Inquisitor wards his mind and soul to withstand the inluence of the Archenemy of Mankind. Just as his Acolytes help him to guard Mankind against such damnation, so does he guard them, strengthening their resolve with benedictions of hatred and cleansing prayers. <br />Whenever this character or an ally within 10 metres gains Corruption, reduce the amount gained by 1 to a minimum of 0. In addition, an ally within 10 metres can spend a Fate point to gain 0 Corruption instead. These efects do not stack when there are multiple characters with this talent within range.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Shared Destiny, Shield of Contempt, Hatred (any)","aptitudes":"Defence, Leadership","benefit":"reduce allies corruption taken","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"7i2OTHBqGvu8m4kL"}
{"name":"Mighty Shot","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte knows the weak points in every type of armour and material, and has the skill to ensure that his shots land exactly where they can do the most damage. He adds half his Ballistic Skill bonus (rounded up) to damage he inflicts with ranged weapons.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 40","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Offence","benefit":"Add half BS bonus to ranged damage rolls.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"81nLztv1CALYDhuJ"}
{"name":"Luminen Blast","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The energies charged in the Acolyte&rsquo;s Luminen Capacitors can be expelled in a ranged attack. The character always counts as being equipped with a Pistol weapon with a 10m range. This can only be used in single shot mode, and deals 1d10 plus twice his Willpower bonus in Energy damage, with Pen 0 and the Shocking quality. The character always counts as having Weapon Training for this weapon and after making an attack with it, he must pass a Toughness test or suffer 1 level of Fatigue.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Luminen Shock, Luminen Capacitors, Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Tech","benefit":"May discharge stored energy as a ranged attack.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8LQuCrnQZ4MC6AiK"}
{"name":"Halo of Command","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has trained himself to better to lead and sway others, either motivating or terrifying those around him to greater levels. When targeting friendly NPCs through skills that have either the Social or Leadership Aptitudes (such as Charm, Command, and Intimidate), he can affect those within 100 times his Fellowship bonus in metres rather than 10 times that number.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Fellowship 40, Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Fellowship, Leadership","benefit":"Affect NPCs within 100xFelB metres with  Social skills.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9XJJkxlbFbq2wIOy"}
{"name":"Two-Weapon Master","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has mastered the difficult ability of wielding a weapon in each hand, making him deadly both in personal and shortranged attacks. When armed with two single-handed weapons (such as a pistol or sword in either hand), he ignores the &ndash;20 penalty for Two-Weapon Fighting (see page 228).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 45, Ambidextrous, Ballistic Skill 40 or Weapon Skill 40, Two-Weapon Wielder (Melee, Ranged)","aptitudes":"Finesse, Offence","benefit":"No penalties when fighting with two single- handed weapons.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9pd5uLjqhGzsThBE"}
{"name":"True Grit","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is able to shrug off wounds that would fell lesser men. Whenever he suffers Critical damage (after reduction for Armour and Toughness), reduce the amount by his Toughness bonus (to a minimum of 1 damage).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Toughness 40","aptitudes":"Toughness, Defence","benefit":"Reduce Critical damage taken.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9sgs7bKDYnAJOIwW"}
{"name":"Eye of Vengeanc","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte can focus his intent on where it is likely to do most damage to his enemy and then strike his foe down with a single shot. Before making a ranged Standard Attack action, he can spend a Fate point. If he does so, he adds the number of degrees of success scored on the attack test to both his damage and penetration for the hit.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 50","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Offence","benefit":"Spend 1 Fate point to increase damage and penetration.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AbJWHU5tW0VwiBAv"}
{"name":"Crushing Blow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has the ability to focus his entire body into close combat attacks. He adds half his Weapon Skill bonus (rounding up) to damage he inflicts with melee attacks.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Offence","benefit":"Add half WS bonus to damage inflicted in melee.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FmsnNtiYkxna637F"}
{"name":"Push the Limit","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whether through study, practice, or sheer intuition, the Acolyte is aware of the limits of his vehicle or steed, and knows how to push it to those limits and beyond. Although overtaxing a beast or executing wheel-tearing turns can provide a great advantage in combat or pursuit, a single wrong move can prove catastrophic, injuring the pilot or even ripping his vehicle apart. Once per round, the character may add +20 to an Operate test (or Survival test in the case of living steeds); however, if he fails the test by 4 or more degrees of failure, immediately roll 1d5 on Table 7&ndash;32: Motive Systems Critical Hit Effects on page 257 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook and apply the result. If he is riding a living mount, roll 1d5 on Table 7&ndash;18: Impact Critical Effects &ndash; Leg on page 239 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook and apply the result.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill, Tech-Use","aptitudes":"Perception, Tech","benefit":"the Acolyte is aware of the limits of his vehicle or steed","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GCI1EbeVnkbbkgtN"}
{"name":"Target Selection","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s dread gaze marks out his chosen victim, and not even the riotous confusion of close combat interferes. He can shoot into melee with no penalty. If he also makes an Aim action beforehand, he prevents any chance of hitting friendly targets as well.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 50","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","benefit":"May shoot into melee without penalty.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KjVKnFVGFHFGtE05"}
{"name":"Instrument of His Will","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte strikes down daemonic foes with holy fury, his blows landing as if guided by the hand of the Emperor Himself. The keen edge of his faith and hatred presents the true threat to the Daemon, not his physical strength or the potency of his weapon.</p>\n<p>Effect: After making a successful attack against a Daemon (this can include striking it with a psychic power), the character may spend a Fate point to increase the damage of the first hit he inflicts as part of that attack by an amount equal to twice his Willpower bonus. This additional damage ignores armour and Toughness bonus.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 50","aptitudes":"Offence, Willpower","benefit":"Fate point for additional dmg against demons","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MM4pTo0en9v4369b"}
{"name":"Delicate Interrogation","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Questioning suspects and witnesses is always a necessary part of any investigation. Such sessions must remain secretive or obscured, however, lest others learn of the Inquisition&rsquo;s interest, and a variety of subterfuges, deceptions, and outright threats come into play to aid this effort. Whenever the Acolyte would decrease his warband&rsquo;s Subtlety due to an interrogation, the amount of Subtlety lost is reduced by 1d5. If this results in a negative number, the Acolyte&rsquo;s skilled efforts increase the warband&rsquo;s Subtlety by 1.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Coordinated Interrogation, Fellowship 50","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Finesse","benefit":"Reduce Subtlety loss by 1d5 when conducting  an investigation.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MbOfDcQoJJQ7Wiiy"}
{"name":"Superior Chirurgeon","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s advanced medical training enables him to knit flesh with deft mastery, essential for treating combat casualties. His exceptional education in use of the Narthecium, Med-Slate, and supplemental drugs give his patients an enormous advantage. He gains a +20 bonus on all Medicae skill tests. When providing first aid, he ignores the penalties for Heavily Damaged patients and only suffers a &ndash;10 penalty for those suffering Critical damage.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 in the Medicae skill","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Gain +20 to Medicae tests, bonuses to first  aid tests.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"NUIPe1pv74FKWEtg"}
{"name":"Never Die","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s will or devotion to the Emperor can sustain him when his mortal body fails. He may spend one Fate point to ignore the effects of injury (such as those from Critical damage), Fatigue, and Stunning for a single combat, so long as they would not kill him immediately. This talent does not prevent the damage, but allows him to temporarily ignore its effects for the duration of the combat. Once the encounter ends, the effects trigger as normal.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 50, Toughness 50","aptitudes":"Toughness, Defence","benefit":"Ignore penalties from Critical damage by  spending Fate point.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ODQ9jW91KfHBqXCN"}
{"name":"Preternatural Speed","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is a swift-moving bringer of death, a living, bloody scythe before whom foes die like corn before the reaper. When making a Charge action, he doubles his normal Charge movement (for instance, if he has an Agility bonus of 3 and thus a Charge movement of 9 metres, his movement is then doubled to 18 metres with this talent).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 40, Agility 50","aptitudes":"Agility, Offence","benefit":"Double speed when charging.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RRDVXI7wcGzRl7Hs"}
{"name":"Dark Soul","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whether through devotion to the Emperor, sheer willpower, single-minded dedication to his duty, or the blessing of some dark power, the Acolyte&rsquo;s internal corruption remains outwardly invisible. With no mutations to mark him as accursed, the Acolyte can continue his radical work without detection.</p>\n<p>Effect: When the character would test to gain a mutation as a result of increasing Corruption, he may choose to automatically pass the test. If he does, he also gains a Malignancy and increases his Corruption total by 1d10.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Hardened Soul, 20 Corruption points","aptitudes":"Toughness, Willpower","benefit":"Mutation is not enough","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WfSFSWjuXiWZACjW"}
{"name":"Assassin Strike","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The character&rsquo;s natural agility and graceful martial form turn him into a dervish of death in combat. After making a melee attack, a successful Challenging (+0) Acrobatics skill test allows the Acolyte to move at half rate as a Free Action. He may only make this move once per round, and the character&rsquo;s opponent does not receive a free attack resulting from this move.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Acrobatics, Agility 40","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Fieldcraft","benefit":"After melee attack, test Acrobatics to move.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XcegVd62UZFM2LnA"}
{"name":"Into the Jaws of Hell","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Inquisitor&rsquo;s strength of conviction and faith in the Emperor&mdash; or perhaps the fear of his retribution&mdash;inspire those at his side to fight on, even in the face of overwhelming odds and the terrors of the galaxy. Servants and allies within 10 metres can subtract the Inquisitor&rsquo;s Fellowship bonus from their degrees of failure on a failed Fear or Pinning test, so long as the Inquisitor passes the test. If this reduces the degrees of failure to 0 or less, a character counts as having passed the test with 1 degree of success. The efects of this talent apply to Acolytes in the Inquisitor&rsquo;s warband and to other servants of the Imperium fighting under the Inquisitor&rsquo;s orders, as well as others at the GM&rsquo;s discretion.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Adamantium Faith, Halo of Command, Will of the Inquisitor","aptitudes":"Leadership, Willpower","benefit":"The Inquisitor inspires those who follow him, to resist fear","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XgFvfuNSwEPjmfCN"}
{"name":"Sanctic Purity","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Sanctic Daemonology is often considered the most pure of psychic disciplines. Practitioners can seem beyond the dangers of the Warp that all too often plague other psykers. Such mastery is taxing, but an experienced Daemonologist can resist the influence of the Warp where other psykers would succumb.</p>\n<p>Effect: When the character triggers Psychic Phenomena when manifesting a power from the Sanctic Daemonology discipline, he may spend a Fate point in order to negate the result entirely.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Daemonologist, Favoured by the Warp, Willpower 50","aptitudes":"Psyker, Willpower","benefit":"spent a fate point do negate a special Psychic Phenomena event","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"bhTPpsx0gN6U0xJ2"}
{"name":"Thunder Charge","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte charges into combat using his body as an additional weapon. Driven by his rage and momentum, the impact of such a charge can knock foes flying or bring them to their knees. When he makes a Charge action, he can barrel through enemies to get to his target. The character makes an Opposed Strength test against each foe in his way (those who his movement would take him past or through). Each foe that loses the Opposed test is knocked Prone. After resolving these Opposed tests, the character&rsquo;s Charge action resolves against his original target as normal.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Strength 50","aptitudes":"Strength, Offence","benefit":"Break enemies with armoured charge.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"cF5vWGgul8XXXSxY"}
{"name":"Daemonic Disruption","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Untouchable&rsquo;s very presence is anathema to Daemons, and only the strongest can threaten him. Creatures of the Warp that lay claw upon the Untouchable must struggle to maintain their hold in reality, lest mere contact hurl them back into the Immaterium.</p>\n<p>Effect: Whenever a creature with the Warp Instability trait makes a successful attack test against this character, it must immediately test for Warp Instability after resolving the attack.&nbsp;</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Bane of the Daemon, Willpower 50, Untouchable elite advance","aptitudes":"Willpower","benefit":"forces Warp Instability rolls","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"guumJQlgiiOoMYVd"}
{"name":"Indomitable Conviction","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>An Inquisitor must often share a part of his burden of knowledge and understanding with those who serve alongside him. Although some Acolytes might succumb to madness and despair, those who undergo such mental trials with their sanity intact come out stronger for it. An Inquisitor can also beneit from such an experience, drawing strength from his comrades and renewing his faith in his duty to Mankind. Whenever this character or an ally within 10 metres gains Insanity, reduce the amount gained by 1. In addition, an ally within 10 metres can spend a Fate point to gain 0 Insanity instead. These efects do not stack when there are multiple characters with this talent within range.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Shared Destiny, Strength through Conviction, Resistance (Fear), Jaded","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"Reduce insanity gained","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iXhbAxqCvupJ6OUj"}
{"name":"Divine Protection","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Those who hunt the witch and mutant often prefer to use cleansing fire to purify their unclean enemies. As if to further demonstrate the cleansing power of flame, some such blessed warriors even use flamers and similar weapons when their allies are in the line of fire, yet miraculously leave them unafected. If a supposed ally does succumb to the flames, surely that is only evidence of concealed heresy. When the Acolyte attacks using a weapon with the Spray quality, it only strikes enemies within the area of effect; the attack does not harm allies.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 45, Willpower 35","aptitudes":"Finesse","benefit":"Spray weapons do not harm allies","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jCjhleMRGG3ABF2b"}
{"name":"Weapon Intuition","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>In the prosecution of his duties against the alien, the Acolyte wields the most arcane and rare weapons the Adeptus Mechanicus can craft, and perhaps even takes up the very armaments of the xenos to better combat it. From years of experience, the character can quickly discern the firing mechanisms and balance of even the strangest weapons, regardless of its origin. The character reduces the penalty for using a weapon without the proper training by 10.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Exotic Weapon Training (Any)","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Finesse","benefit":"Use untrained weapons with -10 instead of -20","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jFs1rUUeVbljCZd3"}
{"name":"Flash of Insight","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Despite steady application of logic and careful analysis, some conundrums remain insoluble, but inspiration could come from outside sources, such as reading patterns from wisps of lho smoke or even making direct appeals to the Emperor for guidance. An Acolyte who has trained his mind to process such lateral data can leap to conclusions that direct thinking cannot provide, and thus quash even the most hidden of heresies. When stuck in an investigation, he can spend one Fate point to reveal a single clue or lead to aid in the progression of his efforts.&nbsp;</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Contact Network, Coordinated Interrogation, Intelligence 40","aptitudes":"Perception, Knowledge","benefit":"Spend 1 Fate point to reveal a clue","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jSusCpMR11lmmyPY"}
{"name":"Warp Lock","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has learned to swiftly cut himself off from the Warp to protect himself from harm. Once per game session, he may ignore the Psychic Phenomena he has rolled (including the Perils of the Warp result on Table 6&ndash;2: Psychic Phenomena, see page 196), completely negating its effects. Such rapid dislocation from the Warp, though, is stressful and traumatic to his mind. He suffers 1d5 Energy damage to the Head location (not reduced by Armour or Toughness) as a result, and cannot make any Focus Power tests or sustain other psychic powers until the beginning of his next turn.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Psy rating, Strong Minded, Willpower 50","aptitudes":"Willpower, Psyker","benefit":"Ignore Psychic Phenomenon once per session","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"kBYSUjNkf2hxTco6"}
{"name":"Blademaster","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s mastery of bladed weapons and their martial disciplines has no peer. When attacking with any bladed weapon, including chainswords, axes, and power swords, he can re-roll one missed attack per round.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 30, Weapon Training (any melee)","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Reroll missed attack, once per round.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"mxAORc4zrlvsIawR"}
{"name":"Deathdealer*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Ranged, Melee</p>\n<p>The Acolyte can place his hits where they inflict maximum harm, such as gaps or joints in armour. When this talent is taken, the character selects the Specialisation that matches the prerequisite used in purchase (Melee with Weapon Skill, Ranged with Ballistic Skill). When the character&rsquo;s attack in that combat type inflicts Critical damage, he adds his Perception bonus to the damage result.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 45 or Weapon Skill 45","aptitudes":"Perception, Finesse","benefit":"Add Per bonus to damage inflicted in combat.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qQZymjvkrT7weSXQ"}
{"name":"Shield Wall","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is a master of the art of weapon-and-shield combat. Forgoing the offensive abilities of a second weapon or the advantages of ranged weaponry, he proves the superiority of this most ancient and honourable of fighting styles. His shield seems to always be in the right position to block his foe&rsquo;s strike, leaving his target open for the inevitable counter.</p>\n<p>Effect: When armed with a shield, the character can re-roll one failed Evasion test to Parry an attack per round.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff; color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif;\">Vikings!</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Raise the shield wall!</span><br style=\"color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\" /><span style=\"color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Hold the front line!</span><br style=\"color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\" /><span style=\"color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Fight 'til death!</span></p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ambidextrous, Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Defence, Weapon Skill","benefit":"re-roll one failed Evasion test","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"sJeo7cqPzDwgz4JO"}
{"name":"Favoured by  the Warp","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whenever this character rolls on Table 6&ndash;2: Psychic Phenomena (see page 196), so long as he does not receive the Perils of the Warp result, he may roll a second time and choose which result he receives.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 35","aptitudes":"Willpower, Psyker","benefit":"Roll twice for Psychic Phenomena and  choose result.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"sTUOYiPXsTcm9Igt"}
{"name":"Sprint","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte moves at great speeds, and when taking a Full Move action can move an extra number of metres equal to his Agility bonus. Additionally, whenever he takes a Run action, he may move double the normal distance. If he did so in the previous round, however, he suffers 1 level of Fatigue.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Agility, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Move more quickly in combat.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"tDlN9beBJ4miRKbz"}
{"name":"Infused Knowledge","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has been imbued with a great breadth of lore, either through punishing noetic techniques or by arcane methods kept secret by the guardians of technology and learning. He counts as having all Common Lore and Scholastic Lore skills at rank 1 (Known)&mdash;basically, he knows something about everything. If he wishes to later improve his Lore skills, these advances must be bought using experience points (from rank 1) as normal. He also adds one degree of success to any successful Common or Scholastic Lore tests, due to his ingrained training.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 40, Lore (any one)","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Knowledge","benefit":"Know a little bit about everything.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"te0WgZqBnljBOy1R"}
{"name":"Step Aside","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Swaying his body out of the path of an attack, the Acolyte causes the shot to pass through thin air, or turns his blade mid-swing to deflect a blow. He can make an additional Evasion attempt (either a Dodge or a Parry) once per round. In effect, this gives him a second Reaction that can only be used for Dodge or Parry attempts, allowing two Dodges, two Parries, or a Dodge and a Parry in each turn. However, he can still only attempt a single Dodge or Parry against each individual attack.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 40, Dodge or Parry","aptitudes":"Agility, Defence","benefit":"Can make additional Dodge or Parry attempt.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uf7Ia5W01zynCXX5"}
{"name":"Bastion of Iron Will","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s sheer willpower and psychic focus have become one and the same, over years of practice and training, such that their combined use is second nature. He adds 5 x his psy rating to any Opposed test he makes when defending against psychic powers.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Psy rating, Strong Minded, Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Willpower, Psyker","benefit":"Gain bonus for Opposed tests against  psychic powers.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ujPaSLXU6m0QCwS4"}
{"name":"Hammer Blow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte strikes a single blow with such focus and force that it breaks armour and pulps flesh as it strikes. When he uses an All Out Attack action to make a single melee attack, he can add half his Strength bonus (rounded up) to the weapon&rsquo;s penetration. The attack also counts as having the Concussive (2) weapon quality, to represent the shocking force of the blow&rsquo;s impact.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Crushing Blow","aptitudes":"Strength, Offence","benefit":"Make a thunderous strike with a melee weapon.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"v8Wo8ztI59zAUhES"}
{"name":"Mastery*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Any skill</p>\n<p>The Acolyte has mastered a single skill. He can spend a Fate point to automatically pass a skill test with his chosen skill, provided the final modifier to his skill test is Challenging (+0) or better. He scores a number of degrees of success equal to the characteristic bonus of the skill&rsquo;s associated characteristic. This talent may be taken more than once, each time for a different skill.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 4 in selected skill","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Knowledge","benefit":"May spend Fate point to succeed on test.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wLtL8VLKwvXOXlJn"}
{"name":"Iron Faith","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s faith is as unyielding as plasteel, and it protects him against the unnatural aura of the daemonic. With the strength of his conviction, he faces down the otherworldly terrors of the Warp the way a lesser man might look down the barrel of a lasgun.</p>\n<p>Effect: The character is immune to the effects of the Baneful Presence trait.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Iron Resolve","aptitudes":"Defence, Willpower","benefit":"immune to the effects of the Baneful  Presence","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/3.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ydNqf5hSrTEruztb"}
